United Air Lines
Presents Chef's Gourmet-
on Selected Flights
to the West Coast.
We decided to let our Chefs go wild in the kitchen. And the
result is the most incredible First Class dining experience
that ever hit 30,000 feet. We call these special flights our
Chef's Gourmet Flights.
They include 7 courses and each one gets better than the last.
You start with cocktails mixed the way you like them. An
elegant appetizer of Glazed Chinook Salmon. Famed
Caesar Salad and an entree like Beef Wellington carved from
a cart—a whole filet of beef in a delicate flaky pastry shell.
Austrian pastries like Sacher Torte, Wines and liqueurs.
But the Chef's Gourmet doesn't stop in First Class. Coach
passengers have a choice of entree too, including top sirloin
steak. Cocktails, fine wines and liqueurs are all available
too at nominal cost.
The service is as impeccable as the food. In fact, one of our
chefs will actually be on board selected flights. Any
suggestions? You can chat with him about it! Just call your
Travel Agent or United and say the magic words—
"Chef's Gourmet".
